wikipedia_page.main: James Jardine (29 January 1794 – 13 January 1872) was an English cricketer with amateur status. He was associated with Kent and made his first-class debut in 1827. He was a contractor by profession, his family being connected with the railways.

response: * James Jardine (engineer) (1776–1858), Scottish civil engineer, mathematician and geologist
* James Jardine (Medal of Honor) (1837–1922), Union Army soldier and Medal of Honor recipient
